# 7. execute()

This is where the real work happens.

Signature

```apex
global void execute(
    Database.BatchableContext bc,
    List<Account> scope)
{
}
```

Suppose Batch Size

```
200
```

scope contains

```
200 Accounts
```

Example

```apex
for(Account a : scope)
{
    a.Rating='Hot';
}

update scope;
```

Salesforce repeats execute()

until every record is processed.

