# 11. Database.Stateful

Normally

Variables reset every execute().

Example

```apex
Integer total=0;
```

Execute 1

```
200 records

total=200
```

Execute 2

Variable becomes

```
0
```

Again.

---

Need total records?

Implement

```apex
Database.Stateful
```

Example

```apex
global class BatchDemo
implements Database.Batchable<SObject>,
Database.Stateful
{
    Integer total=0;

    global void execute(...)
    {
        total+=scope.size();
    }

    global void finish(...)
    {
        System.debug(total);
    }
}
```

Without Stateful

```
200
```

With Stateful

```
5000
```

---

When use Stateful?

✔ Count Success

✔ Count Failure

✔ Totals

✔ Statistics

Don't use Stateful

if unnecessary.

It increases serialization overhead.

